  "text": "Another important and often studied source of individual differences is variability. Variability is sometimes operationalized as the within-person variance (or standard deviation) of repeated observations of a variable. However, this definition misses an important distinction: the difference between the overall amplitude of the displacement from equilibrium and the amplitude of the first derivatives [CITATION_1] ). This distinction is illustrated in Figure 13 .",
